l words within a given string while preserving their original order. The pr=
ompt specifically instructs you to use a <b>Stack</b> data structure to acc=
omplish this. The input is a string <code>s</code> containing multiple word=
s separated by single spaces. The output should be the modified string with=
 each word reversed.</p><p></p><h3><b>Problem Breakdown and Solution</b></h=
3><p></p><p>The core idea is to process the input string word by word. For =
each word, you'll use a stack to reverse it. A <b>stack</b> is a Last-In, F=
irst-Out (LIFO) data structure, meaning the last element added is the first=
 one to be removed.
Here's the step-by-step approach to solving this using a stack:</p><ol star=
t=3D"1"><li><p><b>Iterate through the string:</b> Go through the input stri=
ng character by character.</p></li><li><p><b>Identify words:</b> A word is =
a sequence of characters that are not spaces. When you encounter a characte=
r, push it onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>Reverse and print words:</b> W=
hen you encounter a space or reach the end of the string, it signals the en=
d of a word. At this point, the stack contains the characters of the curren=
t word in their original order. To reverse the word, you simply <b>pop</b> =
each character off the stack and print it. Because a stack is LIFO, the cha=
racters will be popped in reverse order, effectively reversing the word.</p=
></li><li><p><b>Handle spaces:</b> After printing a reversed word, if the c=
haracter that triggered the word-ending condition was a space, you must pri=
nt a space to maintain the original spacing between words.</p></li></ol><p>=
Let's walk through an example using the provided sample input: <b>"I am Goo=
D HUmaN"</b></p><ul><li><p><b>'I'</b>: Push 'I' onto the stack. Encounter a=
 space. Pop 'I'. Print 'I'. Print a space.</p></li><li><p><b>'a'</b>: Push =
'a' onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>'m'</b>: Push 'm' onto the stack. Enc=
ounter a space. Pop 'm', then 'a'. Print 'ma'. Print a space.</p></li><li><=
p><b>'G'</b>: Push 'G' onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>'o'</b>: Push 'o' =
onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>'o'</b>: Push 'o' onto the stack.</p></li=
><li><p><b>'D'</b>: Push 'D' onto the stack. Encounter a space. Pop 'D', 'o=
', 'o', 'G'. Print 'DooG'. Print a space.</p></li><li><p><b>'H'</b>: Push '=
H' onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>'U'</b>: Push 'U' onto the stack.</p><=
/li><li><p><b>'m'</b>: Push 'm' onto the stack.</p></li><li><p><b>'a'</b>: =
